Section 5.1: The tabular environment

The tabular environment is the most basic way to create a table in LaTeX and doesn't require any other packages.

\begin{tabular}{|lcr||}
  left aligned column & center column & right column \\
  \hline
  text & text & text \\
  text & text & text \\
\end{tabular}

The parameter (|lcr|| in the example) is called the table speciﬁcation and tells LaTeX how many columns there
